version_description: this song is in the key of D
This is the main chord progression for the full band version of December by Neck Deep if you would like to play this with a capo, place the capo on Fret 3 and Transpose until Bb is G.
this song is in the key of C
It sounds quite soothing on acoustic, especially if finger-picking is involved.

This is just a very simplified way to play it that sounds okay. When I play it like this I skip an intro and just go straight into the song so i did not add one here. I tried the capo on a few different threats and I thought it sounded alright on a few but 3rd threat sounded better in the end in my opinion. I've only seen one chord version of this song and it was quite different so hopefully this can be of some use to someone.
It has the correct chords in standard tuning rather than non-standard with an added intro.
Tuning is more appropriate, makes song easier to play.
